    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the **Stepper** compound component:\n\n---\n\n## What will be created (4 files touched total)\n\n### New files:\n1. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`** — The component\n2. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx`** — Demo\n\n### Registry entries added to:\n3. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts`** — append `stepper` entry before `]`\n4. **`apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts`** — append `stepper-demo` entry before `]`\n\n---\n\n## Component API — 8 sub-components + 1 hook\n\n| Export | Element | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root; holds `StepperContext` (`value`, `onValueChange`, `orientation`) |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Per-step wrapper; holds `StepperItemContext` (`value`, `disabled`, `completed`); sets `data-state` (active/completed/incomplete) and `data-orientation` |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Calls `onValueChange(value)` on click |\n| `StepperIndicator` | `<span>` | Circle; styled via `group-data-[state=*]/stepper-item` Tailwind selectors — muted border (incomplete) → primary outline (active) → filled primary (completed) |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | Step title |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | Muted description text |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | `group-data-[orientation=horizontal]` → `flex-1 h-px`; `group-data-[orientation=vertical]` → `ms-4 w-px h-6`; turns primary on completion |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Optional `value` prop; falls back to `StepperItemContext`; renders `null` when step not active |\n| `useStepper` | hook | Exported for advanced use |\n\n---\n\n## Orientation strategy\n\n- **Horizontal:** `StepperItem` is `flex-row items-center flex-1`; `StepperSeparator` is a `flex-1 h-px` line. Users wrap items in a `<div className=\"flex w-full\">` and put `<StepperContent value=\"…\">` panels after — all inside `<Stepper>` for context.\n- **Vertical:** `StepperItem` is `flex-col`; `StepperSeparator` is a `ms-4 w-px h-6` connector line centered under the 32px indicator. `StepperContent` inside `StepperItem` needs no `value` prop (infers from `StepperItemContext`).\n\n---\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n- **Two contexts** (global + per-item) avoid prop drilling at both levels\n- **No Radix UI dependency** — pure React, no primitive exists for steppers\n- **Styling via CSS group data-attribute selectors** — matches the exact pattern used in `tabs.tsx` and `carousel.tsx`\n- **`StepperContent` value is optional** — flexible for both horizontal (explicit `value`) and vertical (inferred from context)",
